&lt;p&gt;An opportunity had arisen for a Critical Care Practice Development Nurse to join our dynamic team and expanding team. &lt;br /&gt;The next few years will be exciting as Blackpool Teaching hospital Foundation trust uses funding of £2.8m to redesign and build its Emergency and Critical Care Village. We have already embarked on designing our new Critical Care unit, and as this is built we will move to a new location and a new way of working. Staff will need developing and training with all pieces of kit and new devices.&lt;br /&gt;As well as investment in the building there has also been a huge recent investment in staff, and we have expanded our workforce in terms of numbers of nursing staff as well as AHP’s from Dietetics, physiotherapists, Speak and Language therapists and Clinical Psychologist.&lt;br /&gt;This is a dual role of practice development and medical device training, the successful applicant will be responsible for the support of rotational staff, existing staff, students and visiting professionals. We have a proactive PD team who embrace simulation as a way of working, and being involved in simulations would be a part of the role.&lt;br /&gt;The ideal candidate will be organised, enthusiastic and supportive, moving us forward into our exciting future as a highly skilled, strong, motivated team. Experience in Critical Care Nursing is essential&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For informal discussion please contact:&lt;br /&gt;Karen Smith: Matron. 01253952422&lt;br /&gt;Andrew Henson: Practice Development Nurse. 01253955982&lt;br /&gt;Amy Cartmell: Ward Manager. 01253956867&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
